From: Lor|@Shepherd @end|ng |rom Ro@we||P@rk@org (Kern, Lori)
Date: Tue, 6 Sep 2022 11:31:48 +0000
Subject: [Bioc-devel] Broken dependency (corncob) with new version of a
 package (detectseparation)
In-Reply-To: <CAFMWDyOf8VyhBhq71JD7A=4MNgxoKQ5KuXJSmAg-FBRDSx9EUg@mail.gmail.com>
References: <CAFMWDyOf8VyhBhq71JD7A=4MNgxoKQ5KuXJSmAg-FBRDSx9EUg@mail.gmail.com>
Message-ID: <BL1PR12MB5301417BC4E5C5C675D262AFF97E9@BL1PR12MB5301.namprd12.prod.outlook.com>

The Bioconductor builders will require using the updated versions of any package or system dependency so specifying a specific version in the description will not resolve on the Bioconductor builders.

If you do not have a set time frame for corncob making changes or if they even will, then removing corncob methods temporarily seems like an acceptable solution.

Cheers,


